hmConfiguration.description: The Hirschmann Private MIB definitions for Platform devices.

HmAgentLogSeverity.name: HmAgentLogSeverity
HmAgentLogSeverity.description: Severity code used in determining the SysLog Priority value.

PTPTimeInterval.name: PTPTimeInterval
PTPTimeInterval.description: The scaledNanoseconds member is the time interval expressed in units of nanoseconds and multiplied by 2^+16. Positive or negative time intervals outside the maximum range of this data type shall be encoded as the largest positive and negative values of the data type respectively. For example: 2.5 ns is expressed as: (hex) 0x0000 0000 0002 8000
PTPTimeInterval.reference: IEEE P1588 D2.21 Draft Standard for a Precision Clock Synchronization Protocol for Networked Measurement and Control Systems page 18

PTPPortIdentity.name: PTPPortIdentity
PTPPortIdentity.description: The PTPPortIdentity type identifies a PTP port. The first 8 octets within this value specifies the ClockIdentity. The last 2 octetes within this value specifies the port number. For example: '00 80 63 FF FF 00 00 00 00 01'. ClockIdentity is '008063FFFF000000' and port number is '0001'
PTPPortIdentity.reference: IEEE P1588 D2.21 Draft Standard for a Precision Clock Synchronization Protocol for Networked Measurement and Control Systems page 19

PTPClockIdentity.name: PTPClockIdentity
PTPClockIdentity.description: The PTPClockIdentity type identifies a PTP clock. The PTPClockIdentity shall be in the IEEE EUI-64 format. For example: '008063FFFF000000'
PTPClockIdentity.reference: IEEE P1588 D2.21 Draft Standard for a Precision Clock Synchronization Protocol for Networked Measurement and Control Systems page 19

PTPClockQuality.name: PTPClockQuality
PTPClockQuality.description: The PTPClockQuality represents the quality of a clock. The first octet represents the clock class. The second octet represents the clockAccuracy and the last two octets represent the offsetScaledLogVariance For example:
PTPClockQuality.reference: IEEE P1588 D2.21 Draft Standard for a Precision Clock Synchronization Protocol for Networked Measurement and Control Systems page 19

BridgeIdOrNull.name: BridgeIdOrNull
BridgeIdOrNull.description: The Bridge-Identifier as used in the Spanning Tree or Null, if no valid data is available

hmSysVersion.name: hmSysVersion
hmSysVersion.description: This value is a string that contains at least the following data : SW: Version number of software CH: Version number of chassis BP: Version number of backplane

hmSysGroupCapacity.name: hmSysGroupCapacity
hmSysGroupCapacity.description: The hmSysGroupCapacity is the number of groups that can be contained within the chassis. Within each managed chassis/switch, the groups are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to hmSysGroupCapacity. Some groups may not be present in the chassis, in which case the actual number of groups present will be less than hmSysGroupCapacity. The number of groups present will never be greater than hmSysGroupCapacity.

hmSysGroupMap.name: hmSysGroupMap
hmSysGroupMap.description: This string represents the current configuration of the chassis, encoded as an octet string. Each module is represented by a single octet. If the value of a single octet is the ascii representation of the character '1', it indicates that the module represented by that octet is present, if '0', the module is absent. The number of octets in the string is given by hmSysGroupCapacity. If the value of this variable changes, a hmGroupMapChange trap is sent.

hmSysMaxPowerSupply.name: hmSysMaxPowerSupply
hmSysMaxPowerSupply.description: Maximum number of power supplies for this chassis. Within each managed chassis/switch, the groups are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to hmSysMaxPowerSupply.

hmSysMaxFan.name: hmSysMaxFan
hmSysMaxFan.description: Maximum number of fans for this chassis. Within each managed chassis/switch, the fans are uniquely numbered in the range from 0 to hmSysMaxFan.

hmSysGroupModuleCapacity.name: hmSysGroupModuleCapacity
hmSysGroupModuleCapacity.description: Maximum number of modules that an individual group can contain in this system.

hmSysModulePortCapacity.name: hmSysModulePortCapacity
hmSysModulePortCapacity.description: Maximum number of ports that an individual module can contain in this system.

hmSysGroupTable.name: hmSysGroupTable
hmSysGroupTable.description: This table contains variables for a closer description of a group.

hmSysGroupID.name: hmSysGroupID
hmSysGroupID.description: index to identify an interface card. This value is never greater than hmSysGroupCapacity.

hmSysGroupModuleMap.name: hmSysGroupModuleMap
hmSysGroupModuleMap.description: This string represents the current configuration of a group, encoded as an octet string. Each module is represented by a single octet. If the value of a single octet is the ascii representation of the character '1', it indicates that the module represented by that octet is present, if '0', the module is absent. If the character is 'C', then the card is configurable but absent. The ports can be configured and by setting hmSysModStatus to remove(3) the card can be logically removed. The number of bytes in the string is given by hmSysGroupModuleCapacity.

hmSysGroupAction.name: hmSysGroupAction
hmSysGroupAction.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of other(1). A value of reset(2) has the same effect as a power-on sequence (coldstart). When set to resetStats(3), a reset of all statistic counters of the card's ports will be forced. Any other value results in a badValue status code.

hmSysGroupActionResult.name: hmSysGroupActionResult
hmSysGroupActionResult.description: Result of the last activated action. A value of zero indicates that the result is ok. Bits set in the result indicate error conditions.

hmSysGroupIsolateMode.name: hmSysGroupIsolateMode
hmSysGroupIsolateMode.description: Setting this variable to enable(1) separates the group from the rest of the chassis, so that it will act like a standalone-switch.

hmSysGroupSerialNum.name: hmSysGroupSerialNum
hmSysGroupSerialNum.description: The serial number provided by vendor (ASCII).

hmSysGroupActionDelayPreset.name: hmSysGroupActionDelayPreset
hmSysGroupActionDelayPreset.description: Time in seconds until a reset(2) or hotRestart(10) that was triggered over the hmSysGroupAction object is executed. Writing a zero will cancel any scheduled reset.

hmSysGroupActionDelayCurrent.name: hmSysGroupActionDelayCurrent
hmSysGroupActionDelayCurrent.description: If a delayed reset is scheduled this object will incrementing from the start value to zero.

hmSysModuleTable.name: hmSysModuleTable
hmSysModuleTable.description: This table contains variables for a closer description of a module.

hmSysModGroupID.name: hmSysModGroupID
hmSysModGroupID.description: index to identify an interface card. This value is never greater than hmSysGroupCapacity.

hmSysModID.name: hmSysModID
hmSysModID.description: index to identify a module on an interface card. This value is never greater than hmSysGroupModuleCapacity.

hmSysModNumOfPorts.name: hmSysModNumOfPorts
hmSysModNumOfPorts.description: The numberOfPorts is the number of ports contained within the module. Within each module, the ports are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to numberOfPorts.

hmSysModFirstMauIndex.name: hmSysModFirstMauIndex
hmSysModFirstMauIndex.description: value of the first mauIndex used by the module.

hmSysModStatus.name: hmSysModStatus
hmSysModStatus.description: status of hot-pluggable modules, only for PowerMICE. If the value is physical(1), then the module is plugged in, if the value is configurable, the ports can be configured, but the card is absent, with the value remove(3) written to the agent the card can be logically removed.

hmSysModSerialNum.name: hmSysModSerialNum
hmSysModSerialNum.description: The serial number provided by vendor (ASCII).

hmInterfaceTable.name: hmInterfaceTable
hmInterfaceTable.description: This table contains variables for each interface of the switch.

hmIfaceGroupID.name: hmIfaceGroupID
hmIfaceGroupID.description: index to identify an interface card. This value is never greater than hmSysGroupCapacity.

hmIfaceID.name: hmIfaceID
hmIfaceID.description: index to identify an interface within an interface card.

hmIfaceStpEnable.name: hmIfaceStpEnable
hmIfaceStpEnable.description: Enable or disable spanning tree protocol.

hmIfaceLinkType.name: hmIfaceLinkType
hmIfaceLinkType.description: Describes the link type of the interface.

hmIfaceAction.name: hmIfaceAction
hmIfaceAction.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of noAction(1). When set to resetStats(2), a reset of all statistic counters within this interfacecard will be forced.

hmIfaceNextHopMacAddress.name: hmIfaceNextHopMacAddress
hmIfaceNextHopMacAddress.description: The macaddress of the next switch agent reachable via this interface. If the value is 0:0:0:0:0:0, no other switch is seen via this interface.

hmIfaceFlowControl.name: hmIfaceFlowControl
hmIfaceFlowControl.description: Enables or disables flow control per port

hmIfacePriorityThreshold.name: hmIfacePriorityThreshold
hmIfacePriorityThreshold.description: This object is used to support the dot1dTrafficClassTable. It defines the thresholds of the available priority-classes. Starting at MACH Release 2.20 this variable is not used any more.

hmIfaceName.name: hmIfaceName
hmIfaceName.description: User configurable textual description of the interface. On devices which support Power over Ethernet (IEEE 802.af), this object is mapped to pethPsePortType of the RFC3621 MIB.

hmIfaceTrunkID.name: hmIfaceTrunkID
hmIfaceTrunkID.description: If the value of this variable is greater 0 then it belongs to the link aggregation instance with the same index. If the value is 0 no link aggregation uses this interface.

hmIfacePrioTOSEnable.name: hmIfacePrioTOSEnable
hmIfacePrioTOSEnable.description: Enable or disable Priority setting from IP TOS field.

hmIfaceBcastLimit.name: hmIfaceBcastLimit
hmIfaceBcastLimit.description: Broadcast rate: maximum number of broadcasts to be sent on this port within one second, use 0 for no limitation.

hmIfaceUtilization.name: hmIfaceUtilization
hmIfaceUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during the last sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent. The first historyControlInterval (rfc1757) of this interface is used as sampling interval.

hmIfaceUtilizationControlInterval.name: hmIfaceUtilizationControlInterval
hmIfaceUtilizationControlInterval.description: The interval in seconds over which the data is sampled for hmIfaceUtilization. This interval can be any number of seconds between 1 and 3600 (1 hour). The first historyControlInterval (rfc1757) of this interface is used as sampling interval.

hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable.name: hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable
hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable.description: Enabled or disabled the BPDU guard functionality per port. If BPDU guard functionality are global enabled (hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable=enable(1)), and BPDU guard are enabled per port (hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable=enable(1)) and (R)STP are globally enabled and an BPDU are received on the port, then hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus is set to true(1) for this port and IfAdminStatus for this port is set to down(2). Variable hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus can be reset to their original value (=false) with switching BPDU guard functionality globally off. IfAdminStatus can be reset to to their original values up() only manually.

hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus.name: hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus
hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus.description: Advertised the state of BPDU guard functionality for this port. If BPDU guard functionality fot this port is disabled or guard functionality is enabled, but no BPDUs are received on this port, then hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus is set to false(2) for this port. If BPDU is received on an port with enabled BPDU guard functionality for this port (hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable=enable(1)) and globally (hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable=enable(1)) then hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus is set to true(1) and additionally IfAdminStatus for this port is set to down(2). Variable hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus can be reset (to their original values (=false)) with switching BPDU guard functionality globally off. IfAdminStatus can be again reset to to their original values up() only manually.

hmIfaceCapability.name: hmIfaceCapability
hmIfaceCapability.description: Capability of the interface coded as an integer value with each bit representing a special capability. Meaning of the bits: Bit 0: cabletest capability Bit 1: realtime capability according to IEEE 1588.

hmIfaceIngressLimiterMode.name: hmIfaceIngressLimiterMode
hmIfaceIngressLimiterMode.description: The ingress limiter can work in different modes. Mode all limits the complete ingress traffic. Mode bc limits only the ingress broadcast traffic. Mode bc_mc limits the ingress broadcast and multicast traffic. Mode bc_mc_uuc limits the ingress broadcast, multicast and unknown unicast traffic. The limiter is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIfaceIngressLimiterCalculationMode.name: hmIfaceIngressLimiterCalculationMode
hmIfaceIngressLimiterCalculationMode.description: The ingress limiter can measure the traffic on a bytes per second or on a packets per second basis. The limiter calculation mode is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIfaceIngressLimiterRate.name: hmIfaceIngressLimiterRate
hmIfaceIngressLimiterRate.description: The rate of the ingress limiter. The value 0 disables the limiter.

hmIfaceEgressLimiterMode.name: hmIfaceEgressLimiterMode
hmIfaceEgressLimiterMode.description: The egress limiter can work in different modes. Mode all limits the complete egress traffic. Mode bc limits only the egress broadcast traffic. Mode bc_mc limits the egress broadcast and multicast traffic. Mode bc_mc_uuc limits the egress broadcast, multicast and unknown unicast traffic. The limiter is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIfaceEgressLimiterCalculationMode.name: hmIfaceEgressLimiterCalculationMode
hmIfaceEgressLimiterCalculationMode.description: The egress limiter can measure the traffic on a bytes per second or on a packets per second basis. The limiter calculation mode is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIfaceEgressLimiterRate.name: hmIfaceEgressLimiterRate
hmIfaceEgressLimiterRate.description: The rate of the egress limiter. The value 0 disables the limiter.

hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmUpperThreshold.name: hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmUpperThreshold
hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmUpperThreshold.description: Surveys the interface utilization hmIfaceUtilization and generates an alarm for this interfaces, if the given limit is exceeded. A value of 0 disables the alarm generation.

hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmLowerThreshold.name: hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmLowerThreshold
hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmLowerThreshold.description: Surveys the interface utilization hmInfaceUtilization and removes the alarm condition for this interfaces, if the utilization value is below the given limit. A value of 0 disables the alarm removal.

hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmCondition.name: hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmCondition
hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmCondition.description: The alarm condition is given (true), if the given hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmUpperThreshold limit is exceeded by the interface utilization. The alarm condition will be removed, when the interface utilization falls below the hmIfaceUtilizationAlarmLowerThreshold.

hmIfaceCableCrossing.name: hmIfaceCableCrossing
hmIfaceCableCrossing.description: This variable configures the cable crossing on twisted pair cables. When set to 'enable', the port uses the crossover mode. When set to 'disable', the port does not use the crossover mode. 'Unsupported' is shown, if a port does not support cable crossing. It is not possible to set 'unsupported' to any type of port.

hmIfacePhyFastLinkDetection.name: hmIfacePhyFastLinkDetection
hmIfacePhyFastLinkDetection.description: This variable configures the PHY specific fast link detection feature on this port. 'Unsupported' is shown, if a port does not support this feature. It is not possible to set 'unsupported' to any type of port.

hmTrunkTable.name: hmTrunkTable
hmTrunkTable.description: This table contains variables for each trunk of the switch.

hmTrunkID.name: hmTrunkID
hmTrunkID.description: Index to identify a link aggregation instance

hmTrunkInterfaces.name: hmTrunkInterfaces
hmTrunkInterfaces.description: List of interfaces which are aggregated in the trunk. each octet pair contains the slotID and interfaceID. Interfaces are added or deleteted using the variable hmIfaceTrunkID.

hmTrunkAction.name: hmTrunkAction
hmTrunkAction.description: action according to hmIfaceAction which is performed for all interfaces in the trunk

hmTrunkAdminStatus.name: hmTrunkAdminStatus
hmTrunkAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the trunk. if this variable is set to down(2), all interfaces which are aggregated in the trunk are switched off simultaneously. Reading this variable returns up(1) if at least one interface of the trunk is operational (up).

hmTrunkOperStatus.name: hmTrunkOperStatus
hmTrunkOperStatus.description: The operational state of the trunk. Reading this variable returns up(1) if at least one interface of the trunk is operational (up).

hmTrunkLastChange.name: hmTrunkLastChange
hmTrunkLastChange.description: Time since system boot when there was a change in either the operational state of the trunk or the list of aggregated interfaces.

hmSFPTable.name: hmSFPTable
hmSFPTable.description: This table contains variables for each SFP.

hmSfpGroupID.name: hmSfpGroupID
hmSfpGroupID.description: Index to identify a module. This value is never greater than hmSysGroupModuleCapacity.

hmSfpID.name: hmSfpID
hmSfpID.description: Index to identify an interface within a module. This value is never greater than hmSysModulePortCapacity.

hmSfpVendorOUI.name: hmSfpVendorOUI
hmSfpVendorOUI.description: The SFP's vendor IEEE company ID (OUI).

hmSfpSerialNum.name: hmSfpSerialNum
hmSfpSerialNum.description: The SFP's serial number provided by vendor (ASCII).

hmSfpDateCode.name: hmSfpDateCode
hmSfpDateCode.description: The SFP's vendor manufacturing date code. Format is YY:MM:DD.

hmSfpBitRate.name: hmSfpBitRate
hmSfpBitRate.description: The SFP's nominal bitrate in units of MBits/sec. Contains -1 in case of a device read error.

hmSfpTemperature.name: hmSfpTemperature
hmSfpTemperature.description: This signed integer is used to identify the temperature within the SFP in units of centigrade (celsius). Contains -1000 in case of a device read error.

hmSfpTxPower.name: hmSfpTxPower
hmSfpTxPower.description: The SFP's internally measured Tx Power in units of milliWatts. (ASCII representation of floating point number).

hmSfpRxPower.name: hmSfpRxPower
hmSfpRxPower.description: The SFP's internally measured Rx Power in units of milliWatts. (ASCII representation of floating point number).

hmSfpTxPowerInt.name: hmSfpTxPowerInt
hmSfpTxPowerInt.description: The SFP's internally measured Tx Power in units of 1/10 microWatts.

hmSfpRxPowerInt.name: hmSfpRxPowerInt
hmSfpRxPowerInt.description: The SFP's internally measured Rx Power in units of 1/10 microWatts.

hmSfpRxPowerState.name: hmSfpRxPowerState
hmSfpRxPowerState.description: The state of the SFP's internally measured Rx.

hmSfpInfoVersion.name: hmSfpInfoVersion
hmSfpInfoVersion.description: Version of SFP's Hirschmann Information. Contains -1 in case of a device read error.

hmSfpInfoPartNumber.name: hmSfpInfoPartNumber
hmSfpInfoPartNumber.description: Part Number of SFP's Hirschmann Information.

hmSfpInfoPartId.name: hmSfpInfoPartId
hmSfpInfoPartId.description: Part Identifier of SFP's Hirschmann Information.

hmSfpInfoMagic.name: hmSfpInfoMagic
hmSfpInfoMagic.description: 1, if SFP contains vendor specific information by Hirschmann, otherwise 0.

hmSfpSupported.name: hmSfpSupported
hmSfpSupported.description: Indicates if the local agent supports this SFP.

hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_9.name: hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_9
hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_9.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '9/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_50.name: hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_50
hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_50.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '50/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5.name: hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5
hmSfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '62.5/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hmSfpMaxLength_copper.name: hmSfpMaxLength_copper
hmSfpMaxLength_copper.description: Max. usable length for the cable type 'copper' with this SFP in units of meters.

hmSfpTxPowerdBm.name: hmSfpTxPowerdBm
hmSfpTxPowerdBm.description: The SFP's internally measured Tx Power in units of dBm. (ASCII representation of floating point number).

hmSfpRxPowerdBm.name: hmSfpRxPowerdBm
hmSfpRxPowerdBm.description: The SFP's internally measured Rx Power in units of dBm. (ASCII representation of floating point number).

hmSysChassisName.name: hmSysChassisName
hmSysChassisName.description: This displaystring represents the name of the Chassis. Any change of this variable will cause an automatically update of this value on each Basic Board in this Chassis.

hmSysStpEnable.name: hmSysStpEnable
hmSysStpEnable.description: This variable controls the STP operation of the entire switch. To control the STP function of each port use hmIfaceStpEnable

hmSysFlowControl.name: hmSysFlowControl
hmSysFlowControl.description: enables or disables flow control for the switch unit.

hmSysBOOTPEnable.name: hmSysBOOTPEnable
hmSysBOOTPEnable.description: Enable/Disable BOOTP operation. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. When disabled, no BOOTPs are transmitted by the system. When enabled, the system sends BOOTP requests at booting.

hmSysDHCPEnable.name: hmSysDHCPEnable
hmSysDHCPEnable.description: Enable/Disable DHCP operation. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. When disabled, no DHCPs are transmitted by the system. When enabled, the system sends DHCP requests at booting.

hmSysTelnetEnable.name: hmSysTelnetEnable
hmSysTelnetEnable.description: Enable/Disable Telnet operation. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. When disabled, no Telnet sessions are allowed by the system.

hmSysHTTPEnable.name: hmSysHTTPEnable
hmSysHTTPEnable.description: Enable/Disable HTTP connection. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. When disabled, no HTTP is allowed by the system.

hmSysPlugAndPlay.name: hmSysPlugAndPlay
hmSysPlugAndPlay.description: Enable/Disable Plug&Play feature. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. if this variable is set to enable(1), special Plug&Play actions are performed at boot time and after a successful completion the value is automatically reset to the disable(2) state.

hmBcastLimiterMode.name: hmBcastLimiterMode
hmBcastLimiterMode.description: Global configuration of feature broadcast limiter. If enabled, for each port the maximum rate of broadcasts can be specified.

hmSystemTime.name: hmSystemTime
hmSystemTime.description: Time measured in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, January 1, 1970. The clock of the agents may be set using this variable. Changing this variable on one agent automatically updates the value on the other agents in the same chassis.

hmSystemTimeSource.name: hmSystemTimeSource
hmSystemTimeSource.description: Shows the source of the system time.

hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable.name: hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable
hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable.description: This variable controls the BPDU Guard operation of the entire switch (globally). To control the BPDU Guard function of each port use hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable. If BPDU guard functionality are global enabled (hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable=enable(1)), and BPDU guard are enabled per port (hmIfaceStpBpduGuardEnable=enable(1)) and (R)STP are globally enabled and an BPDU are received on the port, then hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus is set to true(1) for this port and IfAdminStatus is set to down(2) for this port. Variable hmIfaceStpBpduGuardStatus can be reset (to their original values (=false)) with switching BPDU guard functionality globally off (hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable=disable(2)). IfAdminStatus can be again reset to to their original values up() only manually. The default value of hmSysStpBPDUGuardEnable is disable(2).

hmSysSTPErrorNumber.name: hmSysSTPErrorNumber
hmSysSTPErrorNumber.description: Advertised the reason why (R)STP could not be switched on. Error reasons are coded as OR operation bit by bit, see values: 0x00 - no errors - (R)STP is switched on, 0x01 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of standby mode, 0x02 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of kopp Local Active, 0x04 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of kopp Slave Active, 0x08 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of kopp Master Active, 0x10 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of sysRingOn and sysRMMode, 0x20 - (R)STP cannot be switched on, because of error if BB_SetParameter is occured.

hmSysSoftwareCapability.name: hmSysSoftwareCapability
hmSysSoftwareCapability.description: This variable shows the capability of the running software. The string is formated as follow: Byte 1 : Always L (for Layer) Byte 2 : 2 or 3 (dependend if the software supports onyl switching (2) or also routing (3)) Byte 3 : E or P (Enhanced or Professional software functionality)

hmDIPSwitchRSRedundancyManager.name: hmDIPSwitchRSRedundancyManager
hmDIPSwitchRSRedundancyManager.description: Status from redundancy manager DIP switch.

hmDIPSwitchMICERedundancyManager.name: hmDIPSwitchMICERedundancyManager
hmDIPSwitchMICERedundancyManager.description: Status from redundancy manager DIP switch.

hmDIPSwitchMICERingPort.name: hmDIPSwitchMICERingPort
hmDIPSwitchMICERingPort.description: Status from ring ports DIP switch. on (1) indicates port 1 on module 1 and port 1 on module 2 are used as ring ports. off (2) indicates port 1 and 2 on module 1 are used as ring ports.

hmDIPSwitchMICEConfig.name: hmDIPSwitchMICEConfig
hmDIPSwitchMICEConfig.description: Status from DIP switch configuration. on (1) indicates DIP switch configuration is enabled. off (2) indicates DIP switch configuration is disabled.

hmSysMaxTrunks.name: hmSysMaxTrunks
hmSysMaxTrunks.description: Maximum number of trunks for this chassis.

hmIngressLimiterEnable.name: hmIngressLimiterEnable
hmIngressLimiterEnable.description: The global ingress limiter can be enabled or disabled.

hmIngressLimiterMode.name: hmIngressLimiterMode
hmIngressLimiterMode.description: The global ingress limiter can work in different modes. Mode all limits the complete ingress traffic. Mode bc limits only the ingress broadcast traffic. Mode bc_mc limits the ingress broadcast and multicast traffic. Mode bc_mc_uuc limits the ingress broadcast, multicast and unknown unicast traffic. The limiter is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIngressUnknUcLimiterMode.name: hmIngressUnknUcLimiterMode
hmIngressUnknUcLimiterMode.description: The global unknown unicast ingress limiter can be enabled or disabled. The limiter is hardware dependend.

hmIngressUnknUcLimiterCalculationMode.name: hmIngressUnknUcLimiterCalculationMode
hmIngressUnknUcLimiterCalculationMode.description: The global unknown unicast ingress limiter can measure the traffic on a bytes per second or on a packets per second basis. The limiter calculation mode is hardware dependend. Not all modes are available on every hardware.

hmIngressUnknUcLimiterRate.name: hmIngressUnknUcLimiterRate
hmIngressUnknUcLimiterRate.description: The rate of the global unknown unicast ingress limiter. The value 0 disables the limiter.

hmEgressLimiterEnable.name: hmEgressLimiterEnable
hmEgressLimiterEnable.description: The global egress limiter can be enabled or disabled.

hmSysMaxUSBPorts.name: hmSysMaxUSBPorts
hmSysMaxUSBPorts.description: Maximum number of USB ports in this chassis.

hmSysSwitchLearning.name: hmSysSwitchLearning
hmSysSwitchLearning.description: Controls address learning by the switch. When disabled the address database of the switch will not be updated with dynamic filtering entries. Static Filtering Entries and Group Registration Entries are not affected.

hmSysSwitchMRU.name: hmSysSwitchMRU
hmSysSwitchMRU.description: The Maximum Receive Unit MRU that can be received by the switch.

hmSysSwitchFastLinkDetection.name: hmSysSwitchFastLinkDetection
hmSysSwitchFastLinkDetection.description: Controls if the fast link detection is enabled or not.

hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnDetection.name: hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnDetection
hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnDetection.description: Controls if detection of address relearns is enabled or not.

hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnThreshold.name: hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnThreshold
hmSysSwitchAddressRelearnThreshold.description: The value of relearnd addresses to signal address relearn threshold exceeded.

hmSysSwitchDuplexMismatchDetection.description: Controls if duplex mismatch detection is enabled or not.

hmSysSwitchFDBFullCounter.name: hmSysSwitchFDBFullCounter
hmSysSwitchFDBFullCounter.description: The number of FDB Full indications that the agent has detected since reboot.

hmSysSwitchFDBHashOptimizingMode.name: hmSysSwitchFDBHashOptimizingMode
hmSysSwitchFDBHashOptimizingMode.description: Mode to optimize the MAC address table hashing algorithm. Which modes can be configured is hardware dependend. After configuration a reboot is needed.

hmSysSwitchServiceModeOperState.description: If enabled, the switch has been separated into two switching areas with the redundant power supply. The two HIPER Ring ports are in area one. The other ports are in area two. Area one is VLAN capable, area two is not VLAN capable.

hmFanTable.description: This table contains all variables related to the fan units of the chassis/switch. For each fan slot exists one instance.

hmFanSysID.name: hmFanSysID
hmFanSysID.description: The value of SysID is assigned so as to uniquely identify a chassis among the subordinate managed objects of the system.

hmFanID.name: hmFanID
hmFanID.description: This Index is used to identify the associated fan.

hmFanState.name: hmFanState
hmFanState.description: Indicates the operational state of the associated fan.

hmPrioTOSEnable.name: hmPrioTOSEnable
hmPrioTOSEnable.description: Global configuration of feature IP-TOS priority to 802.1D-1998 priority. If enabled, the priority of the TOS field is mapped to 802.1D priority

hmPrioMACAddressEnable.name: hmPrioMACAddressEnable
hmPrioMACAddressEnable.description: Global configuration of feature priority by MAC address. If enabled, for each static MAC address a priority could be specified

hmPrioVlan0TagTransparentMode.description: enables or disables the transparent mode for priority tagged frames (frames with VLAN-ID 0) for the switch unit.

hmPrioMACAddressTable.description: Table for assigning priority to MAC addresses

hmPrioMACPriority.description: priority value for the frame with the specific destination MAC address. 0..7: priority 8 : disabled (no priority by MAC address) 9 : discard the frame

hmPrioTrafficClassID.description: This index is used to identify the associated traffic class

hmPrioTrafficClassWeight.description: With this parameter the queue mode of each traffic class can be set. 2..99: weight for WFQ (Weighted-Fair-Queuing) 100: strict priority

hmPrioTosToPrioTable.name: hmPrioTosToPrioTable
hmPrioTosToPrioTable.description: Translation table IP-TOS priority to 802.1D-1998 priority

hmPrioTTPTos.description: This index is used to identify the associated TOS value

hmPrioTTPPrio.name: hmPrioTTPPrio
hmPrioTTPPrio.description: This index is used to identify the associated 802.1D priority

hmCurrentAddressTable.name: hmCurrentAddressTable
hmCurrentAddressTable.description: A table containing filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management or dynamic by GMRP or IGMP Snooping specifying the set of ports to which frames received from specific ports and containing specific destination addresses are allowed to be forwarded. The value of zero in this table as the port number from which frames with a specific destination address are received, is used to specify all ports for which there is no specific entry in this table for that particular destination address. Entries are valid for unicast and for group/broadcast addresses.

hmCurrentAddressEntry.name: hmCurrentAddressEntry
hmCurrentAddressEntry.description: Filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and containing a specific destination address are allowed to be forwarded.

hmCurrentAddress.name: hmCurrentAddress
hmCurrentAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies. This object can take the value of a unicast address, a group address or the broadcast address.

hmCurrentAddressReceivePort.name: hmCurrentAddressReceivePort
hmCurrentAddressReceivePort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port from which a frame must be received in order for this entry's filtering information to apply. A value of zero indicates that this entry applies on all ports of the bridge for which there is no other applicable entry.

hmCurrentAddressStaticEgressPorts.name: hmCurrentAddressStaticEgressPorts
hmCurrentAddressStaticEgressPorts.description: The set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and destined for a specific MAC address, are allowed to be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.) The default value of this object is a string of ones of appropriate length.

hmCurrentAddressEgressPorts.name: hmCurrentAddressEgressPorts
hmCurrentAddressEgressPorts.description: The complete set of ports, to which frames destined for this Group MAC Address are currently being forwarded. This includes Group MAC Addresses which were set statically or which were learnt by GMRP or some other dynamic mechanism. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.) The default value of this object is a string of ones of appropriate length.

hmCurrentAddressStatus.name: hmCurrentAddressStatus
hmCurrentAddressStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. The default value is permanent(3). other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry. permanent(3) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnReset(4) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnTimeout(5) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until it is aged out.

hmRS2OperMode.name: hmRS2OperMode
hmRS2OperMode.description: hmRS2OperMode shows the operational mode of the system: normal: normal mode, standby-active: standby mode, but switch is active, because the master switch is e.g. not reachable, standby-inactive: stand by mode, redundancy-manager-active: redundancy mode and redundancy-manager has closed RS2 ring, redundancy-manager-inactive: redundancy mode and redundancy-manager has opened RS2 ring. If the value changes, a trap is sent.

hmRS2ConfigError.name: hmRS2ConfigError
hmRS2ConfigError.description: RS2hmConfigError indicates a configuration error of the system: no error: no configuration error, error: in normal mode hmConfigError indicates failure of control line or connection of 2 RS2 in normal mode, in stand by mode hmConfigError indicates absence of control line, failure of control line or connection of 2 RS2 in stand by mode.

hmRS2SigRelayState.name: hmRS2SigRelayState
hmRS2SigRelayState.description: hmRS2SigRelayState shows the state of the (non potential) signalling relay in standard mode: off: ok, on: powersupply not ok or linkstate of a port not ok or configuration error, see power supply table or ifMauTable (attribute ifMauMediaAvailable) or hmConfigError for details.

hmSigLinkTable.name: hmSigLinkTable
hmSigLinkTable.description: This table contains all variables to mask an alarm for the signalling relay, produced by a link. The index for a link corresponds with ifMauIfIndex.

hmSigLinkID.description: This index is used to identify the associated link and corresponds with ifMauIfIndex.

hmSigLinkAlarm.name: hmSigLinkAlarm
hmSigLinkAlarm.description: Indicates whether an alarm for the signalling relay of the associated link will be produced or not, so you can mask the value of ifMauMediaAvailable.

hmSigTrapReason.name: hmSigTrapReason
hmSigTrapReason.description: This object identifies the reason for a trap. There are three reasons for a trap: hmRS2ConfigError ifMauMediaAvailable hmPSState The entity which produces the trap, is specified by hmSigReasonIndex.

hmSigReasonIndex.name: hmSigReasonIndex
hmSigReasonIndex.description: This attribute specifies the entity which produces the trap. 1 - n: index of powersupply table / interfaces table 0: config-error.

hmRS2PartnerIpAddress.name: hmRS2PartnerIpAddress
hmRS2PartnerIpAddress.description: This variable can be used to set manually the redundancy partner of the RS2 agent.

hmRS2TopologyTable.name: hmRS2TopologyTable
hmRS2TopologyTable.description: This table describes the topology of rs2-rings.

hmRS2TopologyLinkID.name: hmRS2TopologyLinkID
hmRS2TopologyLinkID.description: This index is used to identify the associated link and corresponds with ifMauIfIndex.

hmRS2TopologyIpAddress.name: hmRS2TopologyIpAddress
hmRS2TopologyIpAddress.description: This variable can be used to set manually the next RS2 agent.

hmRS2ConnectionMirroringStatus.name: hmRS2ConnectionMirroringStatus
hmRS2ConnectionMirroringStatus.description: Set this variable to configure the status of the connection mirroring functionality. The definition of a destination port is not required.

hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortOne.name: hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortOne
hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortOne.description: Set this variable to the first port to be mirrored.

hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortTwo.name: hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortTwo
hmRS2ConnectionMirroringPortTwo.description: Set this variable to the second port to be mirrored.

hmRS2DisableLearningStatus.description: When set to active the Learning Process is disabled, no new Dynamic Filtering Entries are created and exsisting Dynamic Filtering Entries are removed from the Filtering Database. Static Filtering Entries and Group Registration Entries are not affected.

hmRS2SigRelayMode.name: hmRS2SigRelayMode
hmRS2SigRelayMode.description: When set to standard, this is the default, the signalling relay shows the state of hmRS2SigRelayState. When set to manual, the relay is controlled by hmRS2SigRelayManualState.

hmRS2SigRelayManualState.name: hmRS2SigRelayManualState
hmRS2SigRelayManualState.description: When set to on, this is the default, the signalling relay is opened. When set to off the relay is closed.

hmRS2VlanMode.name: hmRS2VlanMode
hmRS2VlanMode.description: Enables/disables the VLAN mode on this device. When enabled the switch will operate in 802.1Q mode, else in 802.1d mode. After setting this variable the switch have to be reset. The default value is disable.

hmRS2VlanStatus.name: hmRS2VlanStatus
hmRS2VlanStatus.description: Shows the current VLAN mode of this device. When enabled the switch operates in 802.1Q mode, else in 802.1d mode.

hmRS2SelftestResult.name: hmRS2SelftestResult
hmRS2SelftestResult.description: Result of the selftest coded as an integer value with each bit representing the result of a different sub part test. Bits set in the result indicate error conditions of the sub part tests. Meaning of the bits: Bit 0: error switch memory

hmRS2SelftestMode.name: hmRS2SelftestMode
hmRS2SelftestMode.description: Mode of the selftest coded as an integer value with each bit representing a special behaviour of the tests. Meaning of the bits: Bit 0: reboot on failure Bit 1: show failure with hmRS2SigRelayState (a trap will be send also) Bit 2: do switch memory test on start up Bit 3: Clear Bit 2 after next reboot if test has been successfully completed

hmRS2PSAlarm.name: hmRS2PSAlarm
hmRS2PSAlarm.description: Enables/disables an alarm for the signalling relay of the powersupply state.

hmRS2RedNotGuaranteedAlarm.name: hmRS2RedNotGuaranteedAlarm
hmRS2RedNotGuaranteedAlarm.description: When enabled the message 'redundancy not guaranteed' will be signalled on the signalling relay.

hmRS4RVlanPortTable.name: hmRS4RVlanPortTable
hmRS4RVlanPortTable.description: This table describes private vlan enhancements of rs2-4r devices.

hmMgmtBusSelected.name: hmMgmtBusSelected

hmSerialNumCpu.name: hmSerialNumCpu

hmAUIModuleID.description: This index is used to identify a specific module.

hmAUIModuleDTEPowerMonitor.name: hmAUIModuleDTEPowerMonitor
hmAUIModuleDTEPowerMonitor.description: This variable shows the DTE Power Monitor DIP switch setting on the AUI module.

hmAUIPortTable.description: This table contains all AUI variables that are port dependend.

hmAUIPortID.name: hmAUIPortID
hmAUIPortID.description: This index is used to identify a specific port.

hmAction.name: hmAction
hmAction.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of other(1). A value of reset(2) has the same effect as a power-on sequence (coldstart). Writing a value of hotRestart(10) leads to a warmstart. When set to resetStats(3), a reset of all statistic counters within the whole switch will be forced. A value of resetFDB(4) will clear the forwarding database. If set to resetARP(5), the ARP table will be flushed. The value gbl-reset(12) will result in a reset of the whole chassis. Any other value results in a badValue status code.

hmActionResult.name: hmActionResult
hmActionResult.description: Result of the last activated action. A value of zero indicates that the result is ok. Bits set in the result indicate error conditions.

hmNetLocalIPAddr.description: IP address of the management agent board. Changing this value will take effect after activating with hmNetAction.

hmNetLocalPhysAddr.name: hmNetLocalPhysAddr

hmNetGatewayIPAddr.name: hmNetGatewayIPAddr

hmNetMask.name: hmNetMask
